  arose out of her participation in the highly publicized Champion Insurance Company scandal.  In furtherance of
  Champion's scheme to conceal from insurance regulators the true financial condition of the company, respondent
  created counterfeit bank records containing financial information she knew to be false.  Noting that respondent's
  criminal conduct involved both misrepresentation and fraud, this court ordered that she be disbarred.</p>

